-> Auto-scaling using Cloud Run
-> Firestore distributed architecture
-> Event-driven notifications
-> Realtime listeners for live updates

7. Security Design
-> Firebase Authentication
-> JWT Token Validation
-> Role-Based Access Control
-> Firestore Security Rules
-> Secure Payment Verification
-> Protected Consultation Sessions

8. Reliability & Fault Tolerance
-> Distributed lock handling
-> Transaction rollback support
-> Stale lock cleanup
-> Retry mechanisms
-> Multi-device synchronization
-> Doctor failover assignment

9. Database Design Overview
-> Collections
-> users
  
  Stores patient and admin details.

-> doctors

  Stores doctor profile and availability.

-> questionnaires

  Stores patient medical history.

-> appointments

  Stores booking details.

-> locks

  Stores temporary slot locks.

-> chat_messages

  Stores realtime consultation chats.

10. Realtime Architecture

-> Real-time synchronization is implemented using Firestore onSnapshot listeners.

Updates include:

-> Slot availability
-> Booking confirmations
-> Notification delivery
-> Chat synchronization
-> Consultation status

